Then several birds fly around calling together.  Normalized to -3 dB except for voice announcement at -10 dB. 24-bit/48 kHz WAV file edited with Ocenaudio. Unfiltered.

A variety of sounds from a flock of Laughing Gulls working along a canal.  The earlier parts of this are a mixture of sounds from adults and juveniles; the last five minutes are predominantly juveniles.  Occasionally (at 4:26 and 6:20) a juvenile attempts the "laughing" call, but the result is hoarse and sounds somewhat like the long call of a Ring-billed Gull.  Normalized to -3 dB except for voice announcement at -10 dB.  24-bit/48 kHz WAV file edited with Ocenaudio.  Unfiltered.
